@node "Functions" "Functions"
@toc "Functions"

                                  Functions

                                   (Menus)

Project/About 
-------------

Shows the About Requester with some information about the Program and
its additions.

Project/Rescan 
--------------

ReScans the Autodoc Path. If You have updatet this directory you don´t have
to restart the program. Just use Rescan.

Project/Hide
------------

Closes the Docreader´s window. To reopen just enter the Hotkey or send the
right exchange message.

Project/Quit 
------------

Will end the program.

Prefs/Prefs 
-----------

Will bring up the Prefs Editor. See Prefs section for detail.

Prefs/LastSaved 
---------------

Resets the preferences to last saved status


                                  (Global)

                All Functions support full keyboard control.

To  View  an  Autodoc  you  have  to  choose  one to show its contents in the
right list.   There  you can select one item to display the function with the
desired textviewer.

To  Display  Synopsis  just  set the cursor on the function in the right list
and press  the  help  key.   Note  that  Multimode will be switched to normal
Viewmode if you use this function.

                                  (Buttons)

Guru 
----

Will decode the 8 Digit Guru Numbers to a user readable format
using identify.library by Richard Körber.

All Guru Numbers are shown in Hex Format, so You have to enter all digits
in Hex, too.

After decoding in the upper information textfield the Alert Type, Error
Class and Subsystem will be displayed. In the lower info textfield the
description will be shown.

Search 
------

Lets You search for a Function through the entire autodocs directory.

Searching can be aborted by pressing ESC. Next entry can be searched by pressing
the >n< key.

LVO 
---

Is an Library Vector Offset <-> Library Function Name (LVO<->LFN) Converter.
To Search for a LFN just enter the LVO without a leading >-< . Numbers can
be entered in Hex (With a leading $) or in decimal.  To Search for a LVO enter
a LFN or a part of it.

Include 
-------

Will show You a desired Include File. If the cursor is in the right list,
a preselection will be performed. If You are in Dos.library for example
the defaultdirectory for the includes will be set to include:dos/ .

ISearch 
-------

Will Search for Include Files. After entering the search string and the
search pattern (Standard Dos Patterns), the routine will search for matching
Include Files. After search is complete all hits will be displayed in the  right
list and can be shown as showing autodocs. If you Change the Sides of  the lists
or just use Quit from the menu this routine ends.

Structs 
-------

After entering a structure name it will be searched in the
provided Structure.Offsets file and if it was found it will also be displayed.

Multisel
--------

In Multimode all selected autodocs will be collected and their names
displayed in the lower left list. If You hit Multimode again all the docs  will
be displayed at once.

@endnode

@node "Prefs" "Prefs"
@toc "Prefs"

                                 Preferences
                                 -----------

By  choosing  the  prefs  item  of the prefs menu the preferences edit window
will be displayed.

CX-POPUP
--------

Indicates if the Program shall bring up its window on startup.

AutoDoc Path / Include Path / FD Path
-------------------------------------

Indicate the paths to the requested directories.

Structs Path
------------

Points to the Structure.Offsets file

Viewer
------

Is Your desired Textviewer to display all the stuff.

Font
----

The prefered Window Font.
Note: It should be a 8 Pixel font. 11 Pixel will match in most cases, too.
      Bigger fonts are not recommended.

CX-PopKey
---------

Indicates the Programs hotkey.

@endnode

